            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\",\"id\":\"msg_01EryEmt8Z6A157N28CNXscM\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Based on my analysis of the Hero.tsx file, here's the JSON response:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"hasForm\\\": true,\\n  \\\"hasL10Import\\\": false,\\n  \\\"hasL10CreateLead\\\": false,\\n  \\\"needsInstrumentation\\\": true,\\n  \\\"summary\\\": \\\"The Hero component has an email input field (line 65-70) and a submit button (line 72-74), but it's missing L10 integration. There's no import of L10 from '@/lib/tracking', no form submission handler, and no L10.createLead() call. The button currently has no onClick handler and the form doesn't prevent default submission or handle the email capture.\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Details:**\\n- ✅ **Has email form**: Yes (Input component with email state management)\\n- ❌ **Has L10 import**: No (missing `import { L10 } from '@/lib/tracking'`)\\n- ❌ **Has L10.createLead()**: No (button has no onClick handler, no form submission logic)\\n- ⚠️ **Needs instrumentation**: Yes - requires adding form submission handler with L10.createLead() call, success/error state management, and user feedback\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":6,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":11087,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":11087,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":287,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
